orities. Numerous tables with selected statistics underscore the economic analysis and black and white photos offer a glimpse on the technical base of the railway sector. The book is filled with enlightening comparisons of the Czechoslovak transportation industry with its counterparts in the whole Eastern Bloc. Integration into the Council for Mutual Economic Assistance (Comecon) of the Bloc could have been an asset, yet the records have more to say about conflicts than cooperation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aRailroadszCzechoslovakiaxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aEastern bloc.  atransportation industry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2022z978311078048240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633864777423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633864777/original  a978-3-11-078048-2  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK